{"claim_type": "reactor-physics", "line_end": 13, "line_start": 13, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The IBM 7090 program NURGATROYD is a revised and extended version of the IBM 704 program PET-I, which solves (by a fifth-order Runge-Kutta procedure) the coupled first-order differential equations for power, delayed neutron concentration and temperature in a one-region reactor as a function of time, given an input reactivity variation represented by a series of linear ramps."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 13, "line_start": 13, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Typical running times are of the order of 12 milliseconds per time step; a calculation of a 30-second power history using a 10 milliseconds time step requires about 36 seconds of machine time."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 28, "line_start": 28, "page_hint": null, "section": "I. Introduction", "text": "This report is a description of an IBM 7090 program based on a particular model of the Molten Salt Reactor Experiment."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 28, "line_start": 28, "page_hint": null, "section": "I. Introduction", "text": "Its previous successful use in the 704 program PET indicated applicability to the present problem and no revision has as yet been found either desirable or necessary."}
